The Trump economy is driving up business optimism, leading to strong growth and productivity, and creating more job opportunities. Small business optimism is at a 35-year high, with records being set for job creation. U.S. small-business owners are more optimistic than ever before, according to the Wells Fargo/Gallup Small Business Index. Retail sales and manufacturing output are powering U.S. growth, and U.S. retail sales have increased strongly in July. Productivity in the U.S. is climbing at the fastest pace in three years, while labor costs are falling. Jobless claims have dropped near a post-recession low, and for the third straight month, there are more job openings than unemployed people in the U.S.